### Customize Payload Drizzle Schema with beforeSchemaInit hook (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/postgres.mdx

This TypeScript code demonstrates how to use the `beforeSchemaInit` hook in Payload CMS's `postgresAdapter` to directly modify the raw SQL schema. It shows examples of adding a new custom table (`my_table`), adding a new column (`customColumn`) to an existing Payload-generated table (`posts`), and adding an index (`customColumnIdx`) to that table. This approach is necessary when `payload generate:db-schema` does not include schema elements defined through other schema hooks.

```typescript
import { postgresAdapter } from '@payloadcms/db-postgres'

postgresAdapter({
  beforeSchemaInit: [
    ({ schema, adapter }) => {
      // Add a new table
      adapter.rawTables.myTable = {
        name: 'my_table',
        columns: {
          my_id: {
            name: 'my_id',
            type: 'serial',
            primaryKey: true,
          },
        },
      }

      // Add a new column to generated by Payload table:
      adapter.rawTables.posts.columns.customColumn = {
        name: 'custom_column',
        // Note that Payload SQL doesn't support everything that Drizzle does.
        type: 'integer',
        notNull: true,
      }
      // Add a new index to generated by Payload table:
      adapter.rawTables.posts.indexes.customColumnIdx = {
        name: 'custom_column_idx',
        unique: true,
        on: ['custom_column'],
      }

      return schema
    },
  ],
})
```

