### Import and Append Existing Tables to Payload Schema in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/postgres.mdx

Demonstrates importing existing database table schemas and appending them to the Payload schema using beforeSchemaInit hook. This approach prevents Payload from dropping existing tables when initializing the database schema.

```typescript
import { postgresAdapter } from '@payloadcms/db-postgres'
import { users, countries } from '../drizzle/schema'

postgresAdapter({
  beforeSchemaInit: [
    ({ schema, adapter }) => {
      return {
        ...schema,
        tables: {
          ...schema.tables,
          users,
          countries,
        },
      }
    },
  ],
})
```

