### Integrate Existing Drizzle Schema via beforeSchemaInit Hook (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/sqlite.mdx

This TypeScript example shows how to use the `beforeSchemaInit` hook to import and append existing Drizzle table definitions, such as `users` and `countries`, into Payload's database schema. This approach is valuable for preserving and integrating pre-existing database structures when migrating to or working with Payload CMS, ensuring full schema compatibility.

```ts
import { sqliteAdapter } from '@payloadcms/db-sqlite'
import { users, countries } from '../drizzle/schema'

sqliteAdapter({
  beforeSchemaInit: [
    ({ schema, adapter }) => {
      return {
        ...schema,
        tables: {
          ...schema.tables,
          users,
          countries,
        },
      }
    },
  ],
})
```

