### Extend Drizzle Schema with Custom Tables using beforeSchemaInit (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/sqlite.mdx

This TypeScript code illustrates the use of the `beforeSchemaInit` hook within the `sqliteAdapter` to extend the Drizzle schema with custom tables not managed by Payload. This allows developers to define and integrate additional database structures, such as `added_table`, before Payload builds its own schema, which is useful for specialized data requirements.

```ts
import { sqliteAdapter } from '@payloadcms/db-sqlite'
import { integer, sqliteTable } from '@payloadcms/db-sqlite/drizzle/sqlite-core'

sqliteAdapter({
  beforeSchemaInit: [
    ({ schema, adapter }) => {
      return {
        ...schema,
        tables: {
          ...schema.tables,
          addedTable: sqliteTable('added_table', {
            id: integer('id').primaryKey({ autoIncrement: true }),
          }),
        },
      }
    },
  ],
})
```

