### Implement Local JSON Schema Validation for Payload JSON Field (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/json.mdx

This code demonstrates how to enforce local JSON schema validation for a Payload JSON field. It integrates a `jsonSchema` object directly into the field configuration, providing a `uri`, `fileMatch`, and the `schema` definition itself to guide the editor and validate data upon saving.

```ts
import type { CollectionConfig } from 'payload'

export const ExampleCollection: CollectionConfig = {
  slug: 'example-collection',
  fields: [
    {
      name: 'customerJSON', // required
      type: 'json', // required
      jsonSchema: {
        uri: 'a://b/foo.json', // required
        fileMatch: ['a://b/foo.json'], // required,
        schema: {
          type: 'object',
          properties: {
            foo: {
              enum: ['bar', 'foobar']
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

